#: intl/datastore:1
msgid "1.     The first item is to determine which accounts are affected by the event.  In this case intuition may be useful in confirming the answer.  The accounts affected are Land, which increases, and cash, which decreases.  Both of these accounts are assets within the balance sheet.  The relevant source documents may include a bill of sale for the Land and a receipt for the cash payment, as well as a canceled check to confirm that the cash has been paid to the seller of the land by the company.  After the end of the year, the company may be audited (if it is a small concern this may not be required) and these source documents may be demanded by the auditors."
msgstr ""

# Article is at <a href="http://translate.khanacademy.org/partner-content/berkeley-digital/accounting-procedures-recording-transactions-financial/accounting-cycle-recording-transactions/a/the-seven-stages-of-the-basic-accounting-cycle">http://translate.khanacademy.org/partner-content/berkeley-digital/accounting-procedures-recording-transactions-financial/accounting-cycle-recording-transactions/a/the-seven-stages-of-the-basic-accounting-cycle</a>.
