msgid "This indicates that the asset land has increased by \\$10,000 and that the asset cash has decreased by \\$10,000.  The counterintuitive use of a debit corresponding to an increase in an asset is due to the origins of accounting in the latin language.  In the original bookkeeping invented by Pacioli (Wikipedia link or similar), increases in assets were written on the left hand side of the tablet or book – in latin, left is translated as debito, which is abbreviated as Debit or “Dr”.  Decreases in assets were written on the right side – translated as credito in latin, and often abbreviated as credit or “Cr”.  The journal, which is sometimes called the general journal is an important document within the accounting system.  It must be updated whenever a business event (termed a transaction) occurs.  It summarizes the understanding of the transaction which the manager arrived at in stage 1.  The journal also forms the raw material for the remaining stages of the accounting cycle."
